The Tsar, Tsarina Alix and their five children were later imprisoned in Siberia before being executed on July 17, 1918. Their remains were exhumed and reinterred in a ceremony on July 17, 1998. What is happening where you live? Find out by adding your postcode or visit InYourArea 69 years ago (1953) Yugoslavia's Marshal Tito became the first communist head of state to visit Britain.He arrived by sea and his ship was escorted up the River Thames to Westminster where he was greeted by the Duke of Edinburgh, Prime Minister Winston Churchill and Foreign Secretary Anthony Eden. 34 years ago (1988) Saddam Hussein launched an illegal chemical attack on the Kurdish city of Halabja, killing between 3,200 and 5,000 civilians. Iraqi planes dropped mustard gas, the nerve agents sarin, tabun and VX and cyanide in what remains the world's deadliest chemical weapons attack on a civilian population.